A young prince in flowing golden robes sits serenely beneath a sprawling Bodhi tree in an ancient Indian palace garden, rendered in the soft watercolor style of Studio Ghibli animation. Lotus flowers float in a tranquil pond nearby, while peacocks roam freely among ornate stone pillars. The scene has a dreamy, incomplete quality with some areas fading into gentle pencil sketch lines and bare paper texture, as if the illustration is waiting to be finished. Warm afternoon light filters through the leaves, casting dappled shadows. The prince's expression is peaceful and contemplative, surrounded by the lush greenery of the Shakya kingdom. Soft pastel colors dominate with touches of saffron, jade green, and dusty rose.
